        "biography": {
            "errors": [],
            "value": "Peruvian researcher, PhD in Biological Sciences, esp. Comparative immunology at the Faculty of Science of the University of Alberta (Canada). Member of the American Society for Virology and the World Society for Virology. Associate professor and member of the Laboratory of Microbiology and Parasitology at Faculty of Veterinary Medicine - UNMSM (Peru). Past sponsored student for Master studies in Peruvian Universities (CONCyTEC-Peru) and by Innovate-Peru for Doctoral studies in Foreign Universities. My research over the last years has focused on mechanisms of genomic characterization of viruses of major relevance for animal and public health, their phylogenetic relationship among other relatives worldwide. Moreover, I study the immune defenses in livestock animals (as Swine, Poultry, Fish, South-American camelids) with emphasis in early immune responses and how they influence the development of long-term immunity. I have worked using multiple molecular techniques such as DNA and RNA extraction, PCR, RT-PCR and real time PCR, electrophoresis; and primary and immortalized cell culture, in vitro functional assays, flow cytometry and others. I have participated in several research projects in my home country (Peru) and in Canada supported by NSERC and ALMA.",
